<br>
I want to roleplay, but Titaisia (and I think most of us) aren't going to tell our life's story to every character who hails us.  If you want to roleplay with someone, think of something to say to them after &quot;Hail, Titaisia.&quot;<br>
<br>
For the people who have been on Firiona Vie longer, there is one thing I think almost all of us could do to improve roleplaying, and it is pretty easy.  Unless you are having a conversation that your characters wouldn't want others to overhear, try to remember not to roleplay in /gsay.  I think just overhearing other people roleplaying will encourage new people that roleplaying does happen, and maybe it will give someone overhearing the conversation a chance to join in the roleplaying a little bit, too.<br>
<br>
Oh!  One last word of warning: consider your race (and class, if it is obvious) when you are roleplaying with someone.  If you are obviously of an evil race or class, for example, maybe that woodelf ranger *is* roleplaying when she ignores you.  Not every character who considers herself your enemy will immediately insult you and challenge you to a duel.<br>
<br>
I hope that helps, and keep trying!)) <p>Captain Titaisia Lightheart<BR>
Jharin officer of her 52nd measure<BR>
"If you're looking for treble, you've found her!"<BR>
